"'''Cantina Communications'''" is a short story written by [[John Chesterman]], originally published in [[Star Wars Official Poster Monthly 16|''Star Wars Official Poster Monthly'' 16]], ''[[The Star Wars Compendium 2: The World of Star Wars]]'', and later archived on [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]].

==Plot summary==
As [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] searches through the crowd at the [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina/Legends|Mos Eisley cantina]], [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] reflects on the various forms of communication used by the different alien species in the room. He recalls his and Obi-Wan's earlier discussion of which species makes the best pilots.

==Continuity==
This article marks the first and only appearance of several alien species, such as the [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] ocean of [[Solanus]], the giant algae beds of the [[Cygnus B system]], [[Klytonian]]s, a particular species of [[olfax]]es, and an unidentified species of emotionless multiple-eyed insectoids described as the best pilots in the galaxy.

